commit.message:
Fixed compilation in static builds.

I've broken static builds in last patch, assuming that all builds were dynamic. This patch addresses that, and enables the new macros only for MSVC builds; also, it forces you to define the LIBRTPROCESS_STATIC preprocessor directive from your project if statically linking the library (again, only for MSVC builds).

Merge pull request #74 from emruiz81/master

Modified sources in order to compile with MSVC compilers:

commit.message:
Modified sources in order to compile with MSVC compilers:
- Declaring arrays in the stack with variable size is not allowed by C standard, although some compilers like GCC allow it, MSVC doesn't. So I've changed all the places where this happen and alloacte a HEAP array instead, but only for MSVC. Non MSVC compilers keep working as before
- Make a DLL interface macro so we can import the library in a standard way
- Added #define NOMINMAX to avoid conflicts with min and max macros in Windows.h
- Disable OMP reduction for now in MSVC, it doesn't work

NOTE: This is NOT enough to compile with MSVC yet, after creating the project files with CMAKE, you need to set the /openmp:experimental compiler flag. I'll try to modify the CMAKE scripts so it is done automatically.
